President Joseph R. Biden Jr. has ordered that the flag of the United States be flown at half-staff as a mark of respect for the victims of the violence that occurred in Lewiston, Maine on October 25, 2023. This order applies to the White House, public buildings and grounds, military posts, naval stations, naval vessels, and other federal government facilities in the District of Columbia, the United States, and its territories and possessions. The flag will remain at half-staff until sunset on October 30, 2023. The order also extends to United States embassies, legations, consular offices, and other facilities abroad, including military facilities and naval vessels and stations.